(7/31/01 2:47:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks everyone</span><hr size=1> Actually tech, if you save as a gif it will look exactly like an uncompressed file type. Just set it to about 8 or 16 colors, that's all you need for lineart, and it should always be at least a little smaller than jpgs, and look MUCH better. I hate when people give jpgs of lineart to color because they always have little fragments all over it, and you have to spend a lot of time cleaning it up. Gif's are far better for lineart.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind I'm talking about inked lineart. If it's a pencil sketch, usually jpg's are better.  <p><table width=100% border=0>
